# Language server protocol support <Badge type=warning text=beta />

The language server protocol (LSP) is a protocol used between an editor or IDE and a language server to provide language features like auto complete, go to definition, find references, etc.

ortfo provides a LSP server that can be used with any editor that supports the LSP.

It allows quality-of-life features like go-to-definition/hover for tags and technologies in description.md files:


![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Installation

Make sure that [ortfodb is installed](/db/getting-started#installation)

## Usage in editors

### Neovim

Add this to your `init.lua`:

```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({'BufEnter', 'BufWinEnter'}, {
		pattern = {"description.md", "*.yaml"},
		callback = function(event)
				print(string.format("starting ortfols for %s", vim.inspect(event)))
				vim.lsp.start {
						name = "ortfo",
						cmd = {"ortfodb", "-c", "/path/to/your/global/configuration/ortfodb.yaml", "lsp"},
						root_dir = vim.fs.dirname(
								vim.fs.find({'ortfodb.yaml'}, { upward = true })[1]
						),
				}
		end
})
```

### VSCode

1. Install the [ortfo extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ortfo.vscode-ortfo)
2. Go to your user settings and set "Ortfo: Global Config Path"
